---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const steps = [
 {
 num: '01',
 title: 'The data lifecycle in practice',
 desc: 'Every GxP system generates data that moves through a lifecycle: creation, processing, review, reporting, retention, and archival. Understanding this lifecycle, and the integrity requirements at each stage, is the foundation of any practical DI program.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'The GxP Data Lifecycle: From Generation to Archival', slug: 'data-lifecycle-and-metadata' },
 ],
 pillar: 'Data Integrity',
 color: '#1C4E80',
 },
 {
 num: '02',
 title: 'Audit trail design and review',
 desc: 'Audit trail requirements are cited in nearly every data integrity warning letter. But what should an audit trail actually capture, and how do you review it efficiently without drowning in volume? This covers both the technical configuration and the review process.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'Audit Trail Design and Review: What FDA Actually Expects', slug: 'audit-trail-design-and-review' },
 ],
 pillar: 'Data Integrity',
 color: '#1C4E80',
 },
 {
 num: '03',
 title: '21 CFR Part 11 and EU Annex 11',
 desc: 'The core regulatory requirements for electronic records and electronic signatures. What each requirement means in practical terms, how the US and EU frameworks differ, and the common misconfiguration patterns that drive findings.',
 articles: [
 { title: '21 CFR Part 11 and EU Annex 11: What They Actually Require', slug: '21-cfr-part-11-eu-annex-11' },
 ],
 pillar: 'CSV & CSA',
 color: '#2F6E4F',
 },
 {
 num: '04',
 title: 'What validation deliverables actually are',
 desc: 'Most validation practitioners can name the documents in a validation package; fewer can explain what purpose each serves and how they relate to each other. This is the reference that explains the "why" behind each deliverable.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'The Validation Deliverable Set: What Each Document Is Actually For', slug: 'validation-deliverables-guide' },
 ],
 pillar: 'CSV & CSA',
 color: '#2F6E4F',
 },
 {
 num: '05',
 title: 'Equipment qualification: DQ through PQ',
 desc: 'Walking through the qualification lifecycle for a real GxP instrument, what each phase proves, what documentation is required, and what the common failure points look like.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'Equipment Qualification: DQ/IQ/OQ/PQ and the Qualification Lifecycle', slug: 'equipment-qualification-lifecycle' },
 ],
 pillar: 'Equipment Qualification',
 color: '#8A5A1E',
 },
 {
 num: '06',
 title: 'Quality risk management in practice',
 desc: 'ICH Q9(R1) provides the framework; FMEA, HACCP, and risk ranking give you the tools. This covers how to apply risk management to DI and validation programs rather than treating it as a theoretical exercise.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'Quality Risk Management: ICH Q9(R1), FMEA, and How to Actually Use It', slug: 'quality-risk-management' },
 ],
 pillar: 'Quality Assurance',
 color: '#6B4E8A',
 },
 {
 num: '07',
 title: 'MES, SCADA, and the shop floor',
 desc: 'Manufacturing automation systems, MES, EBR, SCADA, historians, generate enormous volumes of GxP data with specific audit trail and Part 11 challenges that QC lab-focused programs frequently miss.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'MES, EBR, SCADA, and the Shop Floor: Data Integrity in Manufacturing Automation', slug: 'mes-ebr-scada-data-integrity' },
 ],
 pillar: 'Manufacturing Systems',
 color: '#46566E',
 },
 {
 num: '08',
 title: 'FDA inspection readiness',
 desc: 'Inspection readiness is not about preparing for an inspection, it is about maintaining a state of control that would withstand one at any time. This covers what that actually requires, how to assess readiness, and what the logistics of an FDA inspection look like.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'FDA Inspection Readiness: Building and Maintaining a State of Control', slug: 'fda-inspection-readiness' },
 ],
 pillar: 'Audits & Inspection',
 color: '#9A3B3B',
 },
 {
 num: '09',
 title: 'OOS investigations and laboratory data quality',
 desc: 'Out-of-specification investigations are one of the most regulated activities in pharmaceutical QC. Phase 1 and Phase 2 investigation logic, assignable cause determination, and what FDA inspectors examine.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'OOS Investigation Process: What FDA Expects', slug: 'oos-investigation-process' },
 ],
 pillar: 'Quality Assurance',
 color: '#6B4E8A',
 },
 {
 num: '10',
 title: 'CSV risk assessment: scoping validations correctly',
 desc: 'Risk-based validation is the expectation, not an option. FMEA, criticality scoring, GAMP 5 software categories, and how risk assessment drives testing scope and vendor documentation leverage.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'CSV Risk Assessment Methodology', slug: 'csv-risk-assessment-methodology' },
 ],
 pillar: 'CSV & CSA',
 color: '#2F6E4F',
 },
 {
 num: '11',
 title: 'Supplier and vendor qualification',
 desc: 'Every material, service, and software system has a supplier. Approved vendor lists, qualification tiers, audit programs, quality agreements, and what software vendor qualification requires.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'Supplier and Vendor Qualification', slug: 'supplier-vendor-qualification' },
 ],
 pillar: 'Quality Assurance',
 color: '#6B4E8A',
 },
 {
 num: '12',
 title: 'Change control and revalidation triggers',
 desc: 'Changes to validated systems require documented impact assessment and, in many cases, revalidation. What constitutes a change, how to categorize it, and how to determine testing scope.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'Change Control for Validated Systems', slug: 'change-control-validated-systems' },
 ],
 pillar: 'CSV & CSA',
 color: '#2F6E4F',
 },
 {
 num: '13',
 title: 'Training programs that actually change behavior',
 desc: 'GxP training is a regulatory requirement. But making it effective, not just documented, requires understanding what makes people follow procedures, and what makes them work around them.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'GxP Training Program Design', slug: 'training-program-gxp' },
 ],
 pillar: 'Data Integrity',
 color: '#1C4E80',
 },
 {
 num: '14',
 title: 'AI tools in GxP, what works and what doesn\'t',
 desc: 'An honest assessment of where AI genuinely helps in compliance workflows, what the validation requirements are, and how to design AI tooling that holds up under a GxP audit.',
 articles: [
 { title: 'Building AI Tools for GxP: What Actually Works', slug: 'building-ai-tools-for-gxp' },
 ],
 pillar: 'AI & Automation',
 color: '#7A3B57',
 },
];
---
<Layout title="Implementation Track" description="A sequenced reading path for mid-career GxP practitioners, data lifecycle, audit trails, Part 11, validation deliverables, equipment qualification, and inspection readiness.">
 <div class="page-header track-header">
 <a href="/tracks" class="back-link">← Learning Tracks</a>
 <div class="page-label">Implementation Track</div>
 <h1>Owning Systems: How to Execute</h1>
 <p class="lead">
 This track is for practitioners who already understand GxP basics and want to go deeper into execution: how to design controls, run validations, review audit trails, and build programs that hold up under scrutiny.
 </p>
 <div class="track-meta">
 <div class="track-for-box">
 <span class="for-label">For</span>
 <span>Validation engineers, QA specialists, system owners, lab managers, anyone responsible for the day-to-day execution of GxP quality programs.</span>
 </div>
 <div class="prereq">
 <span class="prereq-label">Prerequisites</span>
 New to GxP? Start with the <a href="/tracks/foundations">Foundations Track</a> first.
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>

 <ol class="steps">
 {steps.map(step => (
 <li class="step">
 <div class="step-num" style={`color: ${step.color}`}>{step.num}</div>
 <div class="step-content">
 <div class="step-pillar" style={`color: ${step.color}`}>{step.pillar}</div>
 <h2 class="step-title">{step.title}</h2>
 <p class="step-desc">{step.desc}</p>
 <div class="step-articles">
 {step.articles.map(a => (
 <a href={`/articles/${a.slug}`} class="step-article-link">
 <span class="article-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
 <span>{a.title}</span>
 </a>
 ))}
 </div>
 </div>
 </li>
 ))}
 </ol>

 <div class="next-track">
 <div class="next-inner">
 <div class="next-copy">
 <div class="next-label">When you're ready</div>
 <h2>Continue to the Advanced Track</h2>
 <p>The Advanced track covers program architecture, inspection defense, 483 response, and what it takes to build and lead a mature DI program.</p>
 </div>
 <a href="/tracks/advanced" class="btn-primary">Advanced Track →</a>
 </div>
 </div>
</Layout>

<style>
 .track-header { position: relative; }
 .back-link {
 font-size: 0.78rem;
 color: var(--muted);
 font-family: var(--mono);
 text-transform: uppercase;
 letter-spacing: 0.08em;
 display: inline-block;
 margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
 transition: color 0.15s;
 }
 .back-link:hover { color: var(--navy); }

 .track-meta {
 display: flex;
 flex-direction: column;
 gap: 0.85rem;
 margin-top: 1.75rem;
 }

 .track-for-box {
 display: flex;
 gap: 0.85rem;
 align-items: baseline;
 font-size: 0.92rem;
 color: var(--body);
 line-height: 1.6;
 background: var(--paper-2);
 border: 1px solid var(--line);
 border-left: 3px solid var(--navy);
 border-radius: var(--radius);
 padding: 0.9rem 1.2rem;
 max-width: 42rem;
 }
 .for-label {
 flex-shrink: 0;
 font-family: var(--mono);
 font-size: 0.66rem;
 font-weight: 500;
 text-transform: uppercase;
 letter-spacing: 0.12em;
 color: var(--navy);
 padding-top: 0.15rem;
 }

 .prereq { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); }
 .prereq-label {
 font-family: var(--mono);
 font-size: 0.66rem;
 font-weight: 500;
 text-transform: uppercase;
 letter-spacing: 0.12em;
 color: var(--brass);
 margin-right: 0.6rem;
 }
 .prereq a { color: var(--link); }
 .prereq a:hover { color: var(--link-h); }

 /* ── Step list ── */
 .steps {
 list-style: none;
 padding: 0;
 margin: 0 0 5rem;
 display: flex;
 flex-direction: column;
 }
 .step {
 display: grid;
 grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr;
 gap: 1.75rem;
 padding: 2.25rem 0;
 border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
 }
 .step:first-child { padding-top: 1.5rem; }
 .step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

 .step-num {
 font-family: var(--mono);
 font-size: 1.5rem;
 font-weight: 500;
 line-height: 1;
 padding-top: 0.2rem;
 letter-spacing: -0.02em;
 }

 .step-pillar {
 font-family: var(--mono);
 font-size: 0.68rem;
 font-weight: 500;
 text-transform: uppercase;
 letter-spacing: 0.12em;
 margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
 }

 .step-title {
 font-family: var(--serif);
 font-size: 1.35rem;
 font-weight: 500;
 color: var(--ink);
 letter-spacing: -0.01em;
 margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
 line-height: 1.25;
 }

 .step-desc {
 font-size: 0.95rem;
 color: var(--body);
 line-height: 1.7;
 margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
 max-width: 44rem;
 }

 .step-articles { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }

 .step-article-link {
 display: flex;
 align-items: center;
 gap: 0.65rem;
 font-family: var(--sans);
 font-size: 0.9rem;
 font-weight: 500;
 color: var(--link);
 padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
 background: var(--surface);
 border: 1px solid var(--line);
 border-radius: var(--radius);
 box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
 transition: border-color 0.15s, color 0.15s, transform 0.15s;
 text-decoration: none;
 }
 .step-article-link:hover {
 border-color: var(--link);
 color: var(--link-h);
 transform: translateY(-1px);
 }
 .article-icon {
 font-family: var(--mono);
 font-size: 0.85rem;
 color: var(--brass);
 flex-shrink: 0;
 }

 /* ── Next-track CTA ── */
 .next-track {
 background: var(--surface);
 border: 1px solid var(--line);
 border-radius: var(--radius);
 box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
 padding: 2.25rem;
 }
 .next-inner {
 display: flex;
 justify-content: space-between;
 align-items: center;
 gap: 2rem;
 }
 .next-label {
 font-family: var(--mono);
 font-size: 0.7rem;
 font-weight: 500;
 color: var(--brass);
 text-transform: uppercase;
 letter-spacing: 0.14em;
 margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
 }
 .next-copy h2 {
 font-family: var(--serif);
 font-size: 1.4rem;
 font-weight: 500;
 color: var(--ink);
 margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
 line-height: 1.2;
 }
 .next-copy p {
 font-size: 0.92rem;
 color: var(--muted);
 line-height: 1.65;
 max-width: 34rem;
 }
 .next-track .btn-primary { flex-shrink: 0; white-space: nowrap; }

 @media (max-width: 600px) {
 .step { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.75rem; }
 .step-num { font-size: 1.25rem; padding-top: 0; }
 .next-inner { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
 .next-track .btn-primary { width: 100%; justify-content: center; }
 }
</style>
